@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Introduction@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   AlarmClock is a small proggie that alarms at a specified time, by
   playing a MP3. It has many nice features:
   @{B}*@{UB} MUI interface. (Using MUIRexx!)
   @{B}*@{UB} It uses very little memory.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's small.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's very easy to use.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Disclaimer" "Disclaimer"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Disclaimer@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   You are using this program at your own risk. I'm NOT responsible for
   anything this program might do. (@{B}Although it shouldn't do any damage!@{UB})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Copyright" "Copyright"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Copyright@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   AlarmClock is ©Copyright Lorens Johansson 1999.
   This program is E-Mailware... If you use it then please send me an E-Mail
   so I can see how many people who uses this program... That's all I ask.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Requirements@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · AmigaOS 2.0+ (Since ARexx was introduced in 2.0)
   · MUI installed.
   · You must have MUIRexx installed and a MUIRexx assign to it.
   · You must have MPega installed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to install@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · Copy the AlarmClock directory wherever you want.
   · Be sure that you have MUIRexx: assigned to where MUIRexx is.
   · That's it!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowTo" "How to Use"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to Use@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   Please E-Mail me if you have any trouble with this program, and I'll
   do my best to help you!

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to Use - Main Window@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                               T H E   G U I
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    @{B}* Alarm:@{UB}
      @{U}Normal Time:@{UU}
        Choose the hour to the left, and the minute to the right
    @{B}* Alarm:@{UB}
      @{B}* Alarm Type:@{UB}
        Select which type of alarm to alarm!
      @{B}* Play MP3:@{UB}
        @{U}MPega:@{UU}
          Select the path to MPega.
        @{U}Options:@{UU}
          Select the options for MPega.
        @{U}MP3:@{UU}
          Select the MP3 file to play.
      @{B}* DisplayBeep:@{UB}
        @{U}Number of times:@{UU}
          Select how many times it should beep!
        @{U}Wait between beeps:@{UU}
          Select how many tenths of a second to wait between beeps!
      @{B}* Play16:@{UB}
        @{U}Play16:@{UU}
          The path to Play16!
        @{U}Options:@{UU}
          The Play16 options!
        @{U}File:@{UU}
          The file to play!
    @{B}* Start:@{UB}
      Starts the alarm... Just wait (sleep)!
    @{B}* About:@{UB}
      Opens the About window.
    @{B}* Quit:@{UB}
      Quits AlarmClock.
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                              T H E   M E N U
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    @{B}* Project:@{UB}
      @{U}* About:@{UU}
        Opens the About window.
      @{U}About MUI:@{UU}
        Shows the MUI about requester.
      @{U}MUI Prefs...@{UU}
        Brings up the MUI preferences...
      @{U}Settings...@{UU}
        @{U}Load Settings@{UU}
          Loads the settings.
        @{U}Save Settings@{UU}
          Saves the settings.
      @{U}Quit:@{UU}
        Quits the program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{B}1.0:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-06-15 ( 3994 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Made the MUI interface.
   · Wrote the Guide.
   · Made it work... :)

   @{B}1.1:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-06-19 ( 8095 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can now save the prefs!
   · Made it smarter when getting the time at start. (Faster to!)
   · Added the possibility to set the alarm after Swatch Beats (Internet
     Time!)
   · Added another typ of alarm, Flash screen and beep. This will use a
     small program by Tommy Lindgren! Thanks!
   · Added an About window. (I forgot, ok? ;) )
   · It will make the window smaller when the alarm is set, and you are
     waiting.

   @{B}1.2:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-06-21 ( 9782 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It now support keyfiles! So register!! (It's free!)

   @{B}1.3:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-09-17 ( 9913 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Removed the Swatch Beats since it didn't work that well (didn't care about
     timezones), thus making it useless!
   · You can now use Play16 as the alarm!
   · Updated my E-Mail address...
@ENDNODE

